    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh convergence study for pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse 1.5 mm, medium 0.8 mm, fine 0.4 mm, and very fine 0.2 mm global element size) were evaluated. Von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction and construct stiffness were monitored as convergence metrics. The Richardson extrapolation method was applied to quantify the grid convergence index (GCI). Results indicated that the fine 0.4 mm mesh achieved convergence with GCI < 1.2% for stiffness and < 2.8% for peak stress, confirming discretization error was within acceptable bounds for the medium credibility level target.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
