      "name": "QoI comparison: FEA vs. experimental compression-bending",
      "description": "Predicted construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement were compared against N=11 experimental measurements across two independent laboratories. All three QoIs satisfied the <10% mean difference criterion and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance bound. Mean stiffness error: 4.2%; mean yield force error: 6.8%; mean force at 40 mm error: 5.1%. The mesh convergence study (activity nagaraja-mesh-convergence-study) confirmed that discretization error contributed less than 1% to the total model uncertainty budget, supporting the validity of these comparisons.",
