      "description": "Combined simulation and experimental uncertainty was propagated using a Monte Carlo approach (n=1000 samples) covering material property variability, geometric tolerance, and boundary condition uncertainty. The validation metric E/uval was computed for each QoI. Maximum E/uval across all three QoIs was 1.41, below the 1.96 threshold. Material property sensitivity dominated the uncertainty budget at 62%. The mesh convergence study outputs were referenced in the uncertainty budget narrative but the associated evidence artifact was logged separately under the bench validation activity.",
